properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 18 at 5:47PM MST until February 19 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Pueblo CO
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...El Paso county.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM MST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
Please use extra caution tonight if you will be going out
tonight.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Areas of dense fog were occurring over
parts of El Paso county early this evening, especially in the
northeastern parts of Colorado Springs. CDOT web cams and
weather stations were indicating visibility of 1/4 of a mile or
less. Dense fog conditions are likely to become more widespread
as moist southeast upslope flow continues over El Paso county.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST WEDNESDAY
